Document: Script
Path: godot/classes/class_script.rst
Summary: Base class for all script objects, providing the foundation for GDScript, C#, and other scripting languages to extend Object functionality.

Inherits: Resource < RefCounted < Object
Inherited By: CSharpScript, GDScript, ScriptExtension

Description:
A class stored as a resource. A script extends the functionality of all objects that instance it. The new method of a script creates a new instance. Object.set_script extends an existing object, if that object's class matches one of the script's base classes.

Properties:
source_code (String): The script source code or an empty string if source code is not available. With the setter, the script is compiled from the source.

Methods:
Method: can_instantiate() -> bool
Returns true if the script can be instantiated.

Method: get_base_script() -> Script
Returns the script directly inherited by this script.

Method: get_global_name() -> StringName
Returns the script's global name, or an empty StringName if the script has no global name.

Method: get_instance_base_type() -> StringName
Returns the script's base type.

Method: has_script_signal(signal: StringName) -> bool
Returns true if the script, or a base class, defines a signal with the given name.

Method: has_source_code() -> bool
Returns true if the script contains valid source code.

Method: instance_has(base_object: Object) -> bool
Returns true if base_object is an instance of this script.

Method: is_abstract() -> bool
Returns true if the script is an abstract script. An abstract script cannot be instantiated and is only used for inheritance.

Method: is_tool() -> bool
Returns true if the script is a tool script. A tool script can run in the editor.

Method: reload(keep_state: bool = false) -> Error
Reloads the script's implementation. If keep_state is true, the current state is saved and restored. Note: This only applies to GDScript.
---CHUNK---
