Document: Script
Path: godot/classes/class_script.rst
Summary: Describes the base Script class in Godot, which serves as the foundation for all scripts and extends object functionality.
Inherits: Resource < Reference < Object
A class stored as a resource. A script extends the functionality of all objects that instantiate it.

This is the base class for all scripts and should not be used directly. Trying to create a new script with this class will result in an error.

The `new` method of a script subclass creates a new instance. Object.set_script() extends an existing object, if that object's class matches one of the script's base classes.
---CHUNK---
