Path: godot/classes/class_script.rst
Summary: Provides methods for inspecting and interacting with script properties and behavior.

Method: can_instantiate() → bool
Returns true if the script can be instantiated.

Method: get_base_script() → Script
Returns the base script if this script extends another one.

Method: get_global_name() → StringName
Returns the global name of the script.

Method: get_instance_base_type() → StringName
Returns the base type of the instances created from this script.

Method: get_property_default_value(property: StringName) → Variant
Returns the default value of a property.

Method: get_rpc_config() → Variant
Returns the RPC configuration for the script.

Method: get_script_constant_map() → Dictionary
Returns a dictionary mapping script constants to their values.

Method: get_script_method_list() → Array[Dictionary]
Returns an array of dictionaries, each describing a method in the script.

Method: get_script_property_list() → Array[Dictionary]
Returns an array of dictionaries, each describing a property in the script.

Method: get_script_signal_list() → Array[Dictionary]
Returns an array of dictionaries, each describing a signal in the script.

Method: has_script_method(method_name: StringName) → bool
Returns true if the script has a method with the given name.

Method: has_script_signal(signal_name: StringName) → bool
Returns true if the script has a signal with the given name.

Method: has_source_code() → bool
Returns true if the script has source code.

Method: instance_has(base_object: Object) → bool
Returns true if the given object is an instance of this script or a script that inherits from it.

Method: is_abstract() → bool
Returns true if the script is abstract and cannot be instantiated directly.

Method: is_tool() → bool
Returns true if the script is a tool script, meaning it runs in the editor.

Method: reload(keep_state: bool = false) → Error
Reloads the script. If `keep_state` is true, attempts to preserve the state of existing instances.
